  "stem": "<p>In the linear function <em>g</em>, g(0) = 6 and g(1) = 11. Which equation defines <em>g</em>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p>g(x) = 5x + 6</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p>g(x) = 6x + 5</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p>g(x) = 11x + 6</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p>g(x) = 5x + 11</p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "a"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. The slope is (g(1) - g(0))/(1 - 0) = (11 - 6)/1 = 5. The y-intercept is g(0) = 6. Therefore g(x) = 5x + 6. The other choices swap or confuse the slope and intercept.</p>",
